item_list.item_description: A monster organ that emits an earsplitting sonic blast when ruptured.
A monster organ that contains a lethal toxin. Handle with extreme care.
A monster organ filled with an extremely potent toxin. Even one touch can be risky.
A monster organ that contains paralyzing neurotoxins.
A monster organ filled with potent neurotoxins. A single touch can cause paralysis.
A monster organ that contains a knockout powder capable of inducing sleep.
A monster organ that contains dangerous powder. One whiff can induce a coma.
A monster organ filled with flammable powder. Handle with extreme care.
A monster organ filled with powder that ignites if it so much as touches air. Danger!
A monster organ that can store up electricity, which is released on impact.
A monster organ that can store up large amounts of high voltage electricity.
A monster internal organ, filled with extremely cold fluid. Handle with care.
A monster organ with tremendous freezing power. Freezes its surroundings.
A monster organ designed to hold and preserve water.
A monster organ designed to hold and preserve copious amounts of water.
Lynian currency, stamped with a pawprint. The letters written on it are foreign.
A priceless ruby formed by the rare hardening of a Felyne hairball.
While unfit for forging, Kelbi horns are a vital component of many items.
Bombadgy body fluid that is prone to bursting into flame. Emitted when in danger.
A big, beautiful feather plucked from a Gargwa. Often used as a fashion accessory.
An antler often used as raw material for armor. Popular with interior decorators.
A Slagtoth hide. It's pretty saggy, helping them evade deadly attacks.
Lustrous hide often cut into large slabs. Prized for its water-resistant properties.
This Kestodon shell's craggy texture helps to fend off attackers.
This sturdy Kestodon shell has grown unusually thick. Feels a bit like a rock.
A Kestodon cranial carapace. Get slammed by this and you're in for a bad time.
A shell that is very strong despite coming from such a small monster.
A carapace grown thick and hard over many years. Super strong for a small monster.
A sturdy part of the skull that yields, shall we say, dashing results?
A pelt from a Bullfango, covered in bristly fur.
A high-quality pelt from a Bullfango. It's as tough as it is bristly.
A Bullfango head, complete with two splendid tusks.
Scale harvested from a Jagras. Famous for its vivid hue and ease of handling.
Precious scale taken from a Jagras. Great for everything from armor to jewelry.
This Jagras skin is easy to work with, making it a great choice for novice craftsmen.
High-quality Jagras skin. Thicker, smoother, but still just as easy to work with.
Zamite skin that feels smooth or coarse depending on which way you rub it.
The hide from the underbelly of a Zamite. Super elastic— just try stretching it.
The hide from the underbelly of a Zamite. The most elastic samples are costly.
A fin that can be all shapes and sizes. The strongest come from the Sandy Plains Delex.
A beautiful, unmarred fin. Its perfection lends it both strength and high value.
Hide that is very resistant to water. Don't expect it to sell for much.
The durable hide of an aquatic monster. Highly Water-resistant, and in especially good shape.
Ludroth sponge that's not fully developed. Popular for many uses besides forging.
A volcanic monster's scale. Highly resistant to fire, but doesn't sell for much.
A high-quality Uroktor scale. Heat-resistant, bright crimson, and popular with the ladies.
Silk shot by Rachnoid. Its high tensile strength makes it stronger than it looks.
High quality silk that is nearly as strong as rope and more flexible too.
Just as useful as sturdy wyvern shell in the hands of a clever craftsman.
The hardest part of the shell. Reveals curious properties when forged.
Difficult to forge with— the results vary depending on which surface you use.
A Bnahabra stinger. It's actually a hollow tube that houses paralytic secretions.
Removing these mouthparts requires a deft hand.
A transparent sac cut from an Altaroth's abdomen, used to store who knows what.
A high-quality sac from an Altaroth's abdomen. It's thin, but durable.
Gajau skin known for its slimy mucus layer. Highly water-resistant.
High-quality Gajau skin. Thick and hard to work with, but it's worth the effort.
Gajau whiskers often used in aquatic gear as they resist water.
High-quality Gajau whiskers. They're so girthy, you could use them for fishing line.
A glossy and subdued black hide taken from a Remobra.
A lustrous and elegant black hide taken from a Remobra.
Unassuming black-and-red hues from a Remobra that some hunters swear by.
The snake-like head of a Remobra. It still looks ready to pounce!
Izuchi hair. Very versatile— you can't go five steps without seeing it somewhere.
High-quality hair taken from an elite Izuchi in the pack. Pleasantly soft to touch.
Izuchi that swing their tail skillfully may become the leader of the pack.
A scale from a Wroggi. Its vivid color warns predators of its venomous properties.
A quality Wroggi scale. The thickness shows this Wroggi lived a long life.
Hide from a Wroggi. You could make some really nice orange leather with this.
A scale from a Baggi. A little tougher than a Jaggi scale.
A quality scale taken from a Baggi. Important for strengthening weapons.
Smooth hide from under a Baggi's scales. Perfect for life in tough environments.
A scale carved from a Jaggi. Popular among hunters for its beauty and versatility.
A vividly-colored superior Jaggi scale that can be used to make hardier equipment.
Hide from under a Jaggi's scales. Cheap, easy to work with, and has numerous uses.
A quality Jaggi hide with a variety of uses. Popular for its beautiful hue.
Hair that grows on an Izuchi's neck and head. Fades from white to orange.
Great Izuchi hair. On top of being gorgeous, it's smooth as a gentle breeze.
This hide of a mature Izuchi is a deep orange fitting for the leader of the herd.
Great Izuchi hide. It's lightweight, strong, and vivid—always a hot item.
A crescent-bladed tail. A flick of the herd leader's tail brings its prey down.
Crescent-bladed tail. Its edge has been honed by the wind to be razor sharp.
Hide from a Great Baggi. Despite how tough it is, it's covered in old scars.
Quality Great Baggi hide. You'd be hard pressed to hurt a Baggi this tough.
A robust Great Baggi claw. It's thicker than a regular old Baggi claw.
A quality Great Baggi Claw. Sharpened by battle, it's perfect for weapons.
A token of an alpha Baggi. The bigger the crest, the stronger they are.
With some fine crafting, the milky white color of these scales can be improved.
Boasts brilliant coloration, and leaves nothing to be desired in strength.
Due to its versatile coloration, this hide is often used in clothing.
Just like the sturdy Kulu hide you know, except stronger, and smoother too.
This beak, developed to eat the yolks out of eggs, has a peculiar shape.
This Kulu beak is a peck above the rest. Stronger than typical wyvern hide.
These feathers are a hit among trendy youth for their vibrant patterns.
These larger, more colorful feathers are often used in decorative items.
Hide from a Great Wroggi. The white-on-orange pattern almost looks dyed.
Quality Great Wroggi hide. The colors would look great on an expert's weapon.
A brace from a Great Wroggi. Covered in scales, it also includes claws and plate.
A tough Great Wroggi brace comprised of high-quality plate and claws.
A beak from a Great Wroggi. Careful with it— it's still poisonous!
An Arzuros pelt. The white portion is soft, while the blue is short and taut.
A splendid Arzuros pelt. Sturdy enough to survive in harsh mountainous terrain.
Shell from an Arzuros's head or back. Bends willingly and is easy to forge.
A quality Arzuros carapace. The thick shell can endure bites from ordinary fangs.
A brace from an Arzuros's forelegs. Its sharp points give forged equipment a wild flavor.
A strong Arzuros brace. Its thorn-like protrusions make paw swipes deadly.
A white pelt carved from a Lagombi. One pat and you'll be hooked on its fluffy fur.
Quality white Lagombi pelt. Its frosty shine makes it a sought-after luxury item.
The long ear of a Lagombi. A lifetime in the cold has made it hard as a shell.
An impressive Lagombi ear. Highly developed, it can be sharp as steel if polished.
Shell piece from a Lagombi's belly. Its ridges allow the Lagombi to slide on ice.
A strong, sticky, and thick Lagombi Plastron. Used to make superior equipment.
A Lagombi claw that's cold to the touch. Permanently covered in ice.
A Lagombi claw surrounded by cold air. Wounds it causes freeze over in an instant.
The heat-resistant shell of a Volvidon. Unaffected even by boiling lava.
A thick Volvidon carapace. The elasticity means forging it requires severe pressure.
A claw from a Volvidon's foreleg. Dramatically raises the power of a wide swing.
A hard, sharp Volvidon claw. Constant exposure to heat has tempered it like steel.
The jagged shell of a Volvidon's back. Its high elasticity makes it ideal for crafting flexible gear.
An Aknosom scale that glows with a stunning ivory light. A popular material.
Armor woven from these beautiful white scales is in demand among royal guards.
Feathered Aknosom scale treasured for its use in umbrellas. Sturdy yet light.
Quality Aknosom feather. Swing it like a blade or layer it into a shield.
An Aknosom comb. The eyeball motif on the forehead shows up in many a ghost story.
Giant and flashy, this Aknosom comb looks like an elegant decorative fan.
Aknosom beak that appears to be wearing lipstick. Used in arts and crafts.
Spongin from a Royal Ludroth's mane. Valued for its elasticity and high water retention.
High-grade elastic hide that boasts a remarkable ability to retain water.
A small scale that enables graceful movement. You need several to forge equipment.
A large, strong scale from a Royal Ludroth. It reflects light in every direction.
A claw from a Royal Ludroth. Adapted better to movement than to attacking.
A sharp, pointed Royal Ludroth claw. It plunges deep into the earth with each step taken.
These crests become rigid when the beast is angry; quantity indicates status.
A proud, strong crest befitting a pack leader. Its sharp horns shine magnificently.
The finned tail of a Royal Ludroth, used by fishermen for their boats.
Shell from a Barroth. It's pretty muddy, but that's why it's so strong.
A Barroth's carapace coated in multiple layers of mud, making it quite rigid.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 Kunai Ask You a Favor?

item_list.item_description: Plate taken from a Barroth's back. Fairly rare, but makes for quality material.
A thick, sturdy part of a Barroth backplate. Mud and sunlight have helped to harden it further.
A Barroth claw. It's not too sharp, but can be used to strengthen many things.
A polished claw sharpened by sand and dirt. It can dig through even the toughest earth.
This durable part of a Barroth's skull is also the hardest to remove.
Barroth tails aren't very valuable, but the meat is hailed as a delicacy.
Mud that Barroth roll around in. Nutrient-rich and great for farming.
Highly nutritious mud. While it makes great fertilizer, it works for weapons too!

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 Kunai Ask You a Favor?

item_list.item_description: Now useable as a material thanks to recent advances. Has mysterious properties.
The hide of a Khezu. Its strange properties are still not fully understood.
These fangs are popular with occult fans and sold on the black market as cursed items.
Having slurped up mounds of flesh, these fangs are used in certain rituals.
The rib bone from a Khezu. Still has chunks of meat attached.
Fatty meat from a Khezu. Looks tasty, but cannot be eaten.
Made from Tetranadon belly, it's very stretchy. Now you can eat as much as you want!
A life of constant combat has made this belly skin sturdy and stretchy as well.
This shell's mossy surface acts as a cushion, making it sturdier than it looks.
Carapace stout enough to send any back-attacking predators packing.
You can store up water in this Tetranadon beak. Great for gear that uses water.
This Tetranadon beak can shoot water at high pressure due to a refined structure.
Disc-shaped bone that protects a Tetranadon's moisturizing organ from foes.
Unscathed, this disc-shaped head bone can fetch a high price as a luxury plate.
Thick fur from around a Bishaten's neck. Protects its neck from hungry jaws.
Quality Bishaten fur that stays orderly under vigorous treatment. High utility.
Bishaten claws may be small, but don't be fooled—they'll tear you to shreds.
These claws are a good omen for those who see the beast as a servant of the gods.
These feathers let Bishaten go wild, providing stability while on their hind legs.
High-quality Bishaten feather. Light blue plumage traces the beast's wild movements.
Bishaten horn resembling a monk's hat. Wearing it makes you smarter, supposedly.
Bishaten horn resembling a monk's hat. The bigger the horn, the slyer the beast.
Tail carapace that is super hard. Can be swung around like a ball on a chain.
Robust tail carapace that is so hard, it can even break through rocks.
Many a hunter has been charmed by the deep forest- green hue of these scales.
Light and sturdy. With a little work, this could let you blend into the woods.
The shade of green varies slightly depending on where it was harvested from.
The surface of this carapace is exceptionally hard; great for making armor.
Green feather taken from a Pukei-Pukei wing. Has many decorative uses.
This wing membrane is highly elastic and resistant to poison, giving it many uses.
A Pukei-Pukei dewlap. Holds a digestive poison that dissolves plants.
Large dewlap that amps up poison production and potency by a large margin.
The striped pattern isn't everyone's cup of tea, but some hunters dig it.
Mud sticks to this scale, building up and increasing its thickness over time.
Sturdy mud-caked Jyuratodus carapace. The mud layer boosts defense greatly.
Once this fang gets a hold of you, it wont let go until you're drowning in mud.
Using this flexible fin, the Jyuratodus is able to easily glide through the mud.
Rock-hard Basarios shell. Can be used to refine metals.
A rigid Basarios shell. The amount of ore in it makes it closer to rock than shell.
The shell that covers a Basarios' torso. Relatively thin and easy to manipulate.
The rigid shell that covers a Basarios' torso. Still thin but far denser than usual.
The wing of a Basarios. Very hard to work as a material.
A stubby Basarios tail composed of minerals more durable than ore.
Faintly pink gems found near the tear ducts of a Basarios.
Somnacanth scale that glistens a brilliant yellow due to its watery coating.
Quality Somnacanth scale that shimmers a brilliant gold under moonlight.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 I Can't Do What Somnacan

item_list.item_description: A spiked Somnacanth carapace built for protection and cutting through water.
This robust carapace lures in victims with its beauty and ruthlessly crushes them.
A claw with a long, hooked shape that's great for weapons, but also farm work!
Somnacanth's well-developed claw. So sharp and tough that it'll easily tear through prey like butter.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 I Can't Do What Somnacan

item_list.item_description: A Somnacanth head-fin. As beautiful as the midnight sea. Careful with the barbs!
In legends, these fins were thought to be the souls of those who had died at sea.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 I Can't Do What Somnacan

item_list.item_description: A glimmering blue powder shot from a Somnacanth's neck. Makes you feel sleepy.
Shimmers like the falling tears of a weeping maiden, ushering in a deep sleep.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 I Can't Do What Somnacan

item_list.item_description: Scales of a Rathian. Their dark emerald hue exudes a feminine grace.
A superior Rathian scale. Looks like a normal Rathian scale, but is much harder.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 Kunai Ask You a Favor?

item_list.item_description: A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.
Rathian shell prized for its lavish green coloration. An excellent armor material.
This heat-resistant material is often used as armor lining.
Needle-like hair found on a Rathian's back and wings. They contain poison.
As sharp as the keenest blade. It is longer and sturdier than other spikes.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 Kunai Ask You a Favor?

item_list.item_description: A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.
A rare, precious gem from inside a wyvern. Almost too nice to use.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★7 Kunai Ask You a Favor?

item_list.item_description: Claws that are moderately difficult to work with. A blacksmith's first test.
Razor-sharp wing talons. Could slice through a tree trunk with ease.
Recent advances allow this marrow to be extracted. It ignites on air contact.
Only recently extractable due to advances in carving techniques. Hard to forge.
White shell from a Barioth. It's strong yet incredibly light.
A Barioth carapace with an impressive shine. Strongly resembles an ice floe.
A white pelt that's soft to the touch. Absorbs impact almost as well as a Barioth.
A high-quality white pelt with a lovely texture. Nobles use it as a symbol of authority.
A deceptively sharp Barioth claw that can carve through thick glaciers.
A claw honed in the harsh Tundra environment. It can take down prey with a single swipe.
These come in many sizes, and assist the Barioth in clinging to walls of ice.
Barioth tails are covered in hard plate, and surprisingly tough to sever.
A fang from a Barioth. Can be used for weapons, but also for decoration.
Amber tusks sharpened by countless kills. Can smash through gigantic ice blocks.
A Tobi-Kadachi scale. Armor made from these is shockingly light.
A quality scale that is flexible as a feather, and light as the wind.
Prone to generating static electricity—its hairs are constantly on end.
The bolt-upright hairs are an indication of the strong electricity flowing inside.
A film that is thin enough to see through, but strong enough to catch the wind.
These sharp-hooked Tobi- Kadachi claws are perfect for zipping up trees.
Tobi-Kadachi use these razor-sharp claws to move around in the trees.
Spikes made of a highly conductive material. Great for gear using electricity.
Conductive electrode that builds up and unleashes purple bolts of electricity.
Sturdy and small Magnamalo scale that is flexible and resistant to fangs.
Glows a piercing purple, imbued with the beast's infinite fighting spirit.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: An armor-like carapace from Magnamalo. Won't budge to any run-of-the-mill strikes.
Carapace hardened by malice. So sturdy, it won't buckle to any attack.
A claw that has grown into a blade shape on Magnamalo's forearm. Already very sharp.
Honed by blood, these arm blades cut prey in two with a single swipe.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: Bladed hide of Magnamalo's back. Its edge is nicked from countless battles.
The blades produced from Magnamalo's back when enraged show its tenacity.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: Majestic Magnamalo horn that echoes with the sorrow of warriors slain.
Horns resembling a general's helmet. Said to grow as one feasts on the defeated.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: Magnamalo's bladed tail. Used to pierce through the guts of unsuspecting prey.
A gaseous crystal that emits flammable gas resembling dancing purple flames.
A crystal of condensed gas. Its quiet exterior belies its savage explosive power.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: Rare Magnamalo scale. Glows with a deep purple, all-consuming menace.
This jewel glows a sinister purple as though holding many unfortunate souls.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 Blazin' Soul of a Warrior

item_list.item_description: Tempered by the heat of an Anjanath, this scale repels any ordinary blade.
Constantly subjected to forge temperatures, these scales are as hard as iron.
This Anjanath fur is used by local firefighters for its fire-resistant properties.
Quality pelt treated as a luxury item for its stoutness and healthy coat.
Fang shaped by the extreme pressure and heat of an Anjanath's mouth.
Fang of a particularly vicious Anjanath. Tears through any and all prey.
Nasal bone of an Anjanath. Its characteristic structure is a hot research topic.
Nasal bones only grow to be this large in beasts that survive countless battles.
This Anjanath tail can be used in weapons, but it's also a local delicacy.
Rare, roiled Anjanath plating, produced by the beast's persistent rage.
Rare jewel from within an Anjanath. Tinged with fire, it shines gallantly.
A scale from a Nargacuga. The surface is covered with the beast's black fur.
A black Nargacuga scale. Despite its hardness, it's surprisingly light and smooth.
Black fur that grows on scales. Covers the animal in jet-black darkness.
Pitch-black fur from a Nargacuga. It absorbs light and emits pure darkness.
A Nargacuga's impressive tail. Might be mistaken for a weapon if seen out of context.
A spiky scale from a Nargacuga tail. It stands up when the beast is enraged.
Blade-like Nargacuga wing. Evolved to cut down prey on the fly.
The large, sharp bladewing of a Nargacuga. It can slice through foes in a flash.
Although small, the jagged placement of these fangs aids their cutting ability.
A Nargacuga's terribly sharp fang. Evolved to tear rather than chew.
Marrow as nimble as the Nargacuga itself; requires talent to properly harvest.
A Nargacuga's medulla. Merely touching it causes extreme pain, making crafting quite difficult.
A transparent Mizutsune scale. Its irregular shape refracts light into many bright colors.
A quality Mizutsune scale. Older scales polished over time can be very valuable.
The purple fur of a Mizutsune. Stiff, but is soft as silk when soaked with bubblefoam.
High-quality purple fur. More foam-absorbent than its lighter counterpart.
A claw that flies freely through bubblefoam, allowing it to be used as a spike.
Friction-reducing bubblefoam helps this deadly claw slice through prey like sushi.
A beautiful brocade-like fin. Males have large fins that turn red to match their mood.
A high-quality fin. Bubble- foam gives it an elegant pattern prettier than dye.
A flowing Mizutsune tail. It's prized for its supple fur and beautiful scales.
Fluid secreted by Mizutsune. Just a few drops can turn a swamp into a bubble bath.
The top layer of Mizutsune fluid. Removes impurities and is used in many rituals.
An ancient scale as old as its former owner. Can even create rainbows from light.
A multicolored orb formed from a crystalized Mizutsune scale and bubblefoam.
This Goss hair repels snow and keeps heat in, making it popular for winter wear.
Goss hair is fought over in snowy lands for its warming and protective qualities.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 An Icy Blade So Bright

item_list.item_description: The Goss Harag's warm body and the cold outside air have tempered this hide.
Freezing air and boiling Goss blood have made this skin harder than most armor.
Goss Harag claws. They grow not only from its toes, but also all over its feet!
These rough claws have stomped through ice and slashed countless beasts.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 An Icy Blade So Bright

item_list.item_description: Ice and snow have built up on this arm carapace until it could work as a weapon.
Arm carapace thickened by the reckless behavior of a Goss Harag.
Lumpy blue horns of a Goss Harag. For some reason, they tend to scare children.
These horns are sometimes seen as bad luck due to their demonic shape.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 An Icy Blade So Bright

item_list.item_description: The Goss Harag melts snow on its body, forming this ice clump on its legs at will.
Any blade or gauntlet made from this ice is sure to freeze children in terror.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 An Icy Blade So Bright

item_list.item_description: A Goss Harag gallbladder once prized as a panacea. Good luck getting it out...

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★8 An Icy Blade So Bright

item_list.item_description: A Rathalos scale. Wyvern scales like this one are fundamental materials.
An extraordinarily durable scale carved from the body of a Rathalos.
A shell piece comprised of layered scales, making it much harder than just one.
This Rathalos shell emanates a nobility befitting the ruler of the skies.
This heat-resistant material is often used as armor lining.
A wing from a Rathalos. Skilled artisans can craft it into strong equipment.
A severed Rathalos tail. It has any number of uses.
A searing tail scale. Hard to come by and as fiery as the wyvern it came from.
A rare, precious gem from inside a wyvern. Almost too nice to use.
Highly water-repellent Almudron scale. Allows for unhindered bog traversal.
A quality Almudron scale. Polished by mud over many years, it's a work of art.
Overlapping scales fused with mud and Almudron mucus to form an outer shell.
You could make a shield from the many hardened layers of bodily fluid and mud alone.
Almudron claws that excel at speedy digging. Dirt fears them.
Sharp Almudron claw that tears through earth like water.
Red tuft of Almudron hair. Covered in a viscous fluid secreted from its pores.
Fin-like tuft of hair that causes mud waves and whirlpools with every move.
These crimson Almudron whiskers sense vibrations to help locate prey.
The longer the whiskers, the better they can sense vibration. Intruders beware.
An impressive Almudron tail. Its willow-esque droop opens up opportunities to strike.
Mud mixed with Almudron mucus. Prized for its viscosity and sumptuous hue.
Mud with high levels of mucus. Coveted by smiths for its miraculous properties.
Rare Almudron scale. As you stare into its gray hue, you feel sucked in.
The contrast of cloudy dull hues and brilliant gold in this jewel is one-of-a-kind.
A blue-green shell which stores electricity and works as a protective insulator.
The carapace of a Zinogre. Its magnificence reveals the futility of facing it.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★6 The Blue Bomber's Best Bud

item_list.item_description: White fur that stores and magnifies electricity, which it holds even after carving.
Zinogre fur said to store lots of electricity. Shines white from the charge.
The Zinogre's magnificent horn, which sends most of nature running for cover.
A pointed Zinogre horn. When carved, it grants equipment incomparable power.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★6 The Blue Bomber's Best Bud

item_list.item_description: A sharp and tremendously powerful claw capable of quickly dicing up prey.
A high voltage Zinogre claw. Its electrified attacks are truly brutal.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★6 The Blue Bomber's Best Bud

item_list.item_description: The plate-covered tail of a Zinogre. It wields deadly force when swung.
The ocher shell that once lined a Zinogre's body. Contains conductive lipids.
An electrically charged Zinogre shell. Grants a thunder god's power to gear.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★6 The Blue Bomber's Best Bud

item_list.item_description: Thunderbugs which have been stimulated by Zinogre. They emit a pale blue light.
A rare and intimidating trophy that seems to pulse with residual fury.
A rare gem sometimes produced inside a Zinogre's body. The beast's power swells within.

quest_rewards.quest_name: E★6 The Blue Bomber's Best Bud

item_list.item_description: Scale from the incredibly violent Tigrex. Incredibly massive and sturdy.
